 An abstract method is a forces its immediate subclass to implement the function of all abstract methods. 
 Where as overriding is optional and is not always a necessity for the subclasses. 
 
 4)
  An abstract class allows you to create functionality that subclasses can implement or override. An interface only allows you to define functionality, not implement it
  
